==============================================================
Computation of the maximum entropy cycle in C^1_18 (Section 4)

Use the programs '1-except/GenerateYZLists1Except'
                 '1-except/maxent-1ex-crossprod'
--------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1: Generate the Y and Z lists:
-------
     ajk@a01:~$ GenerateYZLists1Except.exe 9
     Generating the Y list ...
     Total number of elements in the Y list: 9334080

     Generating the Z list ...
     Total number of elements in the Z list: 11128320


NOTE: The output are two files called:
      freealphalist-1ex-Y.9  and freealphalist-1ex-Z.9

Step 2: Computing alpha x beta for all beta lower or equal
------- than alpha in the files
        freealphalist-1ex-Y.9  and freealphalist-1ex-Z.9

ajk@a01:~$ maxent-1ex-crossprod.exe freealphalist-1ex-Y.9 p18-1ex-Y.out &
ajk@a01:~$ maxent-1ex-crossprod.exe freealphalist-1ex-Z.9 p18-1ex-Z.out &

NOTES: Each of these commands last about one year in the computer we
       used. So, it is imperative to split the task in smaller jobs, as we
       explained in the computation of the maximum entropy cycle for C^0_18.
       This program apart from checking the maximodality of the cycle (that
       in this case has to be done and not for the standard products) also
       saves data each % of the work done to prevent loss of data due to
       computer or power failures. A typical way of splitting the task
       into (for example) four jobs would be:

ajk@a01:~$ maxent-1ex-crossprod.exe freealphalist-1ex-Z.9 p18-1ex-Z-1:1490913.out -f=10.0 -i=1 -e=1490913 -r=0.1 &
ajk@a01:~$ maxent-1ex-crossprod.exe freealphalist-1ex-Z.9 p18-1ex-Z-1490914:3259411.out -f=10.0 -i=1490914 -e=3259411 -r=0.1 &
ajk@a01:~$ maxent-1ex-crossprod.exe freealphalist-1ex-Z.9 p18-1ex-Z-3259412:5564163.out -f=10.0 -i=3259412 -e=5564163 -r=0.1 &
ajk@a01:~$ maxent-1ex-crossprod.exe freealphalist-1ex-Z.9 p18-1ex-Z-5564164:11128320.out -f=10.0 -i=5564164 -e=11128320 -r=0.1 &

********************************** Output *****************************************
Computing maximal entropy of products for period: 18
Listname: freealphalist-1ex-Z.9
Alpha interval checked: ****** to ******
Maximum of entropy found for the following cycles:
11.3212315059573942 (185340 x 211506)
11.3212315059573942 (196302 x 203988)
************************************************************************************

NOTE TO THE OUTPUT: As above, the full information on the elements of the list given
the maximal entropy, the resulting products and the Markov Matrix can be obtained with
the help of the program 'general-products/singleprodinfo'.

